-- Volkswagen Aims for 20% of Indian Car Market by 2018, Handelsblatt Reports
-- B y   C h r i s   R e i t e r
-- 2010-10-05T04:58:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/volkswagen-targets-1-million-car-sales-in-india-by-2018-handelsblatt-says.html
Volkswagen AG  aims to sell 1 million
cars in India by 2018, as it targets 20 percent market share,
 Handelsblatt  reported citing Chief Executive Officer  Martin Winterkorn .  Volkswagen, which has about 2 percent of the Indian car
market, sees demand growing to 5 million vehicles by 2018, the
newspaper reported. The Wolfsburg, Germany-based manufacturer
expects its factory in Pune, which can assemble 110,000 vehicles
a year, to be operating at full capacity by the end of 2011,
Handelsblatt said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chris Reiter in Berlin at 
 creiter2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong at   kwong11@bloomberg.net . 